kpoints/v1` branch\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. **Push Flow: How Checkpoints Get Pushed to Remote**\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go` and `push_common.go`\\n\\n#### PrePush Hook (Entry Point)\\n```\\nUser runs: git push origin main\\n↓\\nGit fires: pre-push hook\\n↓\\nStrategy.PrePush() called with remote name\\n↓\\nTwo branches pushed in parallel:\\n  1. entire/checkpoints/v1 (metadata branch)\\n  2. entire/trails/v1 (trails branch)\\n```\\n\\n#### Push Logic (push_common.go - pushBranchIfNeeded)\\n1. **Check if pushing disabled** via settings (`strategy_options.push_sessions`)\\n   - Defaults to: enabled (auto push)\\n   - Options: `\\\"auto\\\"`, `\\\"prompt\\\"` (ask user), `\\\"false\\\"`/`\\\"off\\\"`/`\\\"no\\\"` (disable)\\n\\n2. **Verify branch exists locally** (refs/heads/entire/checkpoints/v1)\\n\\n3. **Check for unpushed commits**\\n   - Compares local hash vs remote-tracking ref\\n   - If same → skip silently (nothing to push)\\n   - If different → proceed to push\\n\\n4. **Push with retry logic**\\n   - **First attempt**: `git push --no-verify origin entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n   - **On non-fast-forward failure**:\\n     - Runs: `git fetch origin` to get remote state\\n     - **Reconcile disconnected branches** (automatic if branches are orphaned)\\n     - **Build merged tree** from local + remote using checkpoint utilities\\n     - **Create merge commit** with both parents (combining local + remote checkpoints)\\n     - **Update local ref** to merged commit\\n     - **Retry push** → should succeed (now fast-forward)\\n\\n5. **Result**\\n   - Messages to stderr: `[entire] Pushing entire/checkpoints/v1 to origin...`\\n   - Non-blocking: Warnings only, doesn't fail user's push\\n   - Happens **silently in the hook** (user sees no output unless there's an issue)\\n\\n#### Key File: `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go`\\n- `PrePush(ctx, remote)` - Entry point for git pre-push hook\\n- `pushSessionsBranchCommon()` - Checks settings, gates the push\\n- `pushBranchIfNeeded()` - Main push orchestrator\\n- `doPushBranch()` - Handles push + fetch+merge recovery\\n- `tryPushSessionsCommon()` - Actual git CLI push\\n- `fetchAndMergeSessionsCommon()` - Recovery: merges remote into local before retrying\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. **Condensation Flow: Shadow Branch → entire/checkpoints/v1**\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`\\n\\n#### When Condensation Happens\\n1. **PostCommit hook** (after user commits)\\n   - If phase is IDLE or ACTIVE: triggers `EventGitCommit`\\n   - Session state machine decides action (usually `ActionCondense`)\\n\\n2. **Called explicitly** via `strat.CondenseSessionByID(sessionID)`\\n   - Used by `entire attach` command to finalize attached sessions\\n\\n#### Condensation Process: `CondenseSession(ctx, repo, checkpointID, state, committedFiles)`\\n\\n**Input:**\\n- `checkpointID`: 12-hex-char ID from trailer (or generated)\\n- `state`: SessionState with metadata\\n- `committedFiles`: Files in this specific commit (filters which files attach to this checkpoint)\\n- Optional pre-resolved git objects for perf\\n\\n**Output:**\\n- `CondenseResult` with checkpoint ID, session ID, files touched, transcript\\n\\n**Steps:**\\n\\n1. **Extract session data from shadow branch or live transcript**\\n   - Resolves shadow branch: `entire/<commit-hash[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>`\\n   - If shadow exists: reads tree, extracts transcript + prompts\\n   - If no shadow (mid-turn commit): reads live transcript file\\n\\n2. **Extract transcript and filter by checkpoint scope**\\n   - Full transcript from shadow or filesystem\\n   - Slices transcript if `CheckpointTranscriptStart` set (for incremental checkpoints)\\n   - Extracts user prompts from transcript\\n\\n3. **Filter files_touched to committed files** (1:1 checkpoint model)\\n   - If `committedFiles` provided (from PostCommit):\\n     - Only keeps files that overlap with actual commit\\n     - Enables splitting changes across multiple commits\\n   - Otherwise uses session state's full FilesTouched\\n\\n4. **Calculate attribution** (user vs agent changes)\\n   - Compares base commit → shadow branch → HEAD\\n   - Detects which lines user modified vs agent added\\n   - Handles carry-forward (partial commits)\\n\\n5. **Generate summary** (if enabled)\\n   - Uses Claude to summarize transcript\\n   - Stored in metadata\\n\\n6. **Write to permanent storage**\\n   - Calls `store.WriteCommitted()` → writes to `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\\n   - Path: `.entire/checkpoints/v1/<checkpoint_id[:2]>/<checkpoint_id[2:]>/`\\n   - Creates directory structure:\\n     ```\\n     <checkpoint_id[:2]>/<checkpoint_id[2:]>/\\n     ├── metadata.json\\n     ├── full.jsonl          (full transcript)\\n     ├── prompt.txt          (user prompts)\\n     ├── content_hash.txt    (SHA256 of transcript)\\n     └── tasks/<tool-use-id>/ (if task checkpoints exist)\\n     ```\\n\\n#### Key Data in metadata.json\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"checkpoint_id\\\": \\\"a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\",\\n  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"2026-01-13-uuid\\\",\\n  \\\"session_ids\\\": [\\\"...\\\"],  // all sessions in this checkpoint\\n  \\\"session_count\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"manual-commit\\\",\\n  \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\",\\n  \\\"files_touched\\\": [\\\"file1.txt\\\", \\\"file2.txt\\\"],\\n  \\\"author_name\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n  \\\"author_email\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n  \\\"agent\\\": \\\"claude-code\\\",\\n  \\\"checkpoints_count\\\": 3,\\n  \\\"token_usage\\\": { \\\"input_tokens\\\": 1000, \\\"output_tokens\\\": 500 },\\n  \\\"initial_attribution\\\": { \\\"agent_lines\\\": 150, \\\"human_added\\\": 10, ... },\\n  \\\"summary\\\": { \\\"title\\\": \\\"...\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"...\\\" }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key functions:**\\n- `extractSessionData()` - Reads from shadow branch tree\\n- `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript()` - For mid-turn commits\\n- `calculateSessionAttributions()` - Computes user/agent attribution\\n- `buildSessionMetrics()` - Collects performance data\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. **Checkpoint URL Pattern**\\n\\n**Note:** The codebase does NOT currently have web/API integration that exposes checkpoints via URLs like `https://entire.io/gh/entireio/cli/checkpoints/attach-session-id/6ffa85cf0d18`.\\n\\n**What exists:**\\n- Checkpoints are stored in Git (orphan branch `entire/checkpoints/v1`)\\n- Accessible via Git directly: clone repo, checkout branch, read tree\\n- Can be pushed to remote GitHub\\n\\n**What's missing for URL support:**\\n- No web server/API to serve checkpoints\\n- No URL generation/resolution logic\\n- No external session import via URL\\n\\n**Current workflow for external access:**\\n1. Push entire/checkpoints/v1 to GitHub\\n2. Users clone and browse Git history\\n3. Or use CLI tools to read from local git objects\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. **Attach Command: Import External Sessions**\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n\\n**Purpose:** Manually attach an existing agent session (from external IDE) that wasn't captured by hooks\\n\\n**Flow:**\\n\\n```\\n$ entire attach <session-id> [--agent claude-code] [--force]\\n↓\\n1. Validate session ID format\\n2. Check not already tracked\\n3. Resolve agent and transcript path\\n   - Uses agent.Get() to load agent plugin\\n   - Calls agent.ResolveSessionDir() to find transcript\\n   - Falls back to searching alternative project directories\\n4. Read transcript file\\n5. Extract modified files\\n   - Uses agent's TranscriptAnalyzer if available\\n   - Cross-references with git status for actual uncommitted files\\n6. Create session metadata directory\\n   - Path: .entire/sessions/<session-id>/ (in worktree)\\n   - Copy transcript file there\\n7. Initialize session state\\n   - Creates StateStore entry with SessionID, AgentType, StartedAt\\n8. SaveSt