tire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go` | PrePush hook, pushes entire/checkpoints/v1 |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go` | Shared push logic, fetch+merge recovery |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` | CondenseSession: shadow → entire/checkpoints/v1 |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` | Attach command, external session import |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go` | Write to entire/checkpoints/v1 branch |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go` | Shadow branch operations |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go` | Session state storage/loading |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/trailers/trailers.go` | Commit trailer parsing/generation |\\n| `docs/architecture/checkpoint-scenarios.md` | Checkpoint workflows and edge cases |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Current Limitations\\n\\n1. **No URL-based checkpoint access** - Checkpoints exist only in Git, not exposed via web API\\n2. **No external session import via URL** - Attach command only works with local transcripts\\n3. **No checkpoint sharing/collaboration** - Must push to shared Git remote manually\\n4. **Redundant transcript storage** - Each checkpoint stores full transcript (not incremental)\\n5. **Token counting caveat** - Summing token counts across checkpoints double-counts (use last checkpoint only)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Next Steps for URL Support (if implementing)\\n\\nTo implement `https://entire.io/gh/entireio/cli/checkpoints/attach-session-id/6ffa85cf0d18`:\\n\\n1. **Create web service** to serve checkpoints from GitHub\\n2. **Implement checkpoint resolver** that:\\n   - Parses URL format: `gh/<org>/<repo>/checkpoints/<branch>/<checkpoint-id>`\\n   - Clones repo or fetches metadata branch\\n   - Reads sharded checkpoint directory from Git tree\\n   - Returns metadata + transcript JSON\\n3. **Add CLI command** to import from URL: `entire import <url>`\\n4. **Generate shareable URLs** in attach command output\"}],\"totalDurationMs\":75009,\"totalTokens\":85700,\"totalToolUseCount\":25,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":3794,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":77119,\"output_tokens\":4785,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":3794},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"53cd024a-03cf-442d-b5ae-473b511bfd21\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"61b0a478-d835-45a6-936a-9d30f7ba786c\",\"version\":\"2.1.74\",\"gitBranch\":\"attach-session-id\",\"slug\":\"fancy-dreaming-biscuit\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9adf913d-8a24-400b-967b-5bc57f0f0f98\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Agent\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01AMsQk5EWpuyCKhGg4U2AZL\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01AMsQk5EWpuyCKhGg4U2AZL\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:11:44.891Z\",\"uuid\":\"63392dd7-0b58-4a37-ae7f-eef585288305\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"61b0a478-d835-45a6-936a-9d30f7ba786c\",\"version\":\"2.1.74\",\"gitBranch\":\"attach-session-id\",\"slug\":\"fancy-dreaming-biscuit\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c7c59cc0-35f5-483c-bfd5-a96e85093b69\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01AMsQk5EWpuyCKhGg4U2AZL\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent! Let me now create a comprehensive summary document:\\n\\n## Summary Report: Entire CLI Codebase Exploration\\n\\nI have thoroughly explored the Entire CLI codebase to understand the attach command, Gemini agent support, shadow branch creation, checkpoint condensation, and the agent interface. Here are my findings:\\n\\n### 1. THE ATTACH COMMAND\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n\\n**Purpose:** The `entire attach` command allows attaching an existing agent session that wasn't captured by hooks. It creates a checkpoint from the session's transcript and registers the session for future tracking.\\n\\n**Command Usage:**\\n```bash\\nentire attach <session-id> [--agent <agent-name>] [--force]\\n```\\n\\n**Supported agents:** claude-code, gemini, opencode, cursor, copilot-cli, factoryai-droid\\n\\n**How It Works:**\\n1. Validates the session ID format\\n2. Checks that the session isn't already tracked\\n3. Resolves the agent and locates the transcript file\\n4. Reads the transcript and extracts modified files\\n5. Detects file changes via git status\\n6. Creates a session metadata directory and copies the transcript\\n7. Initializes session state via `strat.InitializeSession()`\\n8. Builds a step context with the detected file changes\\n9. Calls `SaveStep()` to create a shadow branch checkpoint\\n10. Condenses the session to permanent storage via `CondenseSessionByID()`\\n11. Transitions the session to IDLE phase\\n12. Offers to amend the last commit with the checkpoint trailer\\n\\n**Key files involved:**\\n- `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/attach.go` - Main attach command implementation\\n- `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/attach_test.go` - Tests for attach command\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. GEMINI AGENT SUPPORT\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/`\\n\\n**Agent Integration:**\\nThe Gemini CLI agent is fully integrated following the `Agent` interface defined in the codebase. It implements:\\n- `Agent` interface - Core agent operations\\n- `HookSupport` interface - Lifecycle hooks\\n- `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface - Transcript parsing\\n- `TokenCalculator` interface - Token usage calculation\\n\\n**Key Implementation Files:**\\n\\n1. **`gemini.go`** - Main agent implementation\\n   - Implements the `Agent` interface\\n   - Stores sessions in `~/.gemini/tmp/<project-hash>/chats/`\\n   - Session transcripts are JSON files: `session-<date>-<shortid>.json`\\n   - `GetProjectHash()` uses SHA256 of project root (matching Gemini CLI's algorithm)\\n   - Implements `ReadTranscript()`, `ChunkTranscript()`, `ReassembleTranscript()`\\n   - Implements `ReadSession()`, `WriteSession()` for session storage\\n   - `ResolveSessionFile()` searches for existing files or constructs filenames\\n\\n2. **`hooks.go`** - Hook installation and management\\n   - Installs 12 hooks in `.gemini/settings.json`\\n   - Hook types: SessionStart, SessionEnd, BeforeAgent, AfterAgent, BeforeModel, AfterModel, BeforeToolSelection, BeforeTool, AfterTool, PreCompress, Notification\\n   - Hooks are executed only when `hooksConfig.enabled` is true\\n   - Commands use matcher patterns (e.g., \\\"exit\\\", \\\"logout\\\" for SessionEnd)\\n   - Supports both production (`entire hooks gemini`) and dev (`go run ... hooks gemini`) modes\\n\\n3. **`lifecycle.go`** - Hook event parsing\\n   - Converts Gemini hooks to normalized lifecycle `Event` objects\\n   - `ParseHookEvent()` handles:\\n     - `SessionStart` → `SessionStart` event\\n     - `BeforeAgent` → `TurnStart` event (with user prompt)\\n     - `AfterAgent` → `TurnEnd` event\\n     - `SessionEnd` → `SessionEnd` event\\n     - `PreCompress` → `Compaction` event\\n     - `BeforeModel` → `ModelUpdate` event (extracts model name)\\n   - Pass-through hooks return `nil` (no lifecycle action)\\n   - Implements `CalculateTokenUsage()` - extracts token counts from transcript messages\\n\\n4. **`types.go`** - Gemini-specific data structures\\n   - `GeminiSettings` - `.gemini/settings.json` structure\\n   - `GeminiHooks` - All hook configurations\\n   - `GeminiHookMatcher` - Matcher patterns for conditional hooks\\n   - `GeminiHookEntry` - Individual hook command entry (requires \\\"name\\\" field)\\n   - Hook input structures: `sessionInfoRaw`, `agentHookInputRaw`, `beforeModelRaw`\\n   - `FileModificationTools` - Lists tools that modify files: write_file, edit_file, save_file, replace\\n   - Token structure: `geminiMessageTokens` (input, output, cached, thoughts, tool)\\n\\n5. **`transcript.go`** - Transcript parsing\\n   - `ParseTranscript()` - Parses Gemini JSON format\\n   - `ExtractModifiedFiles()` - Extracts file paths from tool calls\\n   - `SliceFromMessage()` - Slices transcript from a specific message index\\n   - Gemini format: `{\\\"messages\\\": [...]}`\\n\\n**Agent Registration:**\\nIn `gemini.go` init():\\n```go\\nfunc init() {\\n    agent.Register(agent.AgentNameGemini, NewGeminiCLIAgent)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis self-registers the agent via the global registry without requiring explicit imports.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. AGENT INTERFACE AND REGISTRATION\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/`\\n\\n**Core Agent Interface (`agent.go`):**\\n\\nThe `Agent` interface defines core operations:\\n- **Identity methods:** `Name()`, `Type()`, `Description()`, `IsPreview()`, `DetectPresence()`, `ProtectedDirs()`\\n- **Transcript storage:** `ReadTranscript()`, `ChunkTranscript()`, `ReassembleTranscript()`\\n- **Legacy methods:** `GetSessionID()`, `GetSessionDir()`, `ResolveSessionFile()`, `ReadSession()`, `WriteSession()`, `FormatResumeCommand()`\\n\\n**Optional Interfaces:**\\n\\n1. **`HookSupport`** - For agents with lifecycle hooks\\n   - `HookNames()` - List hook verbs\\n   - `ParseHookEvent()` - Convert hook to normalized Event\\n   - `InstallHooks()`, `UninstallHooks()`, `AreHooksInstalled()`\\n\\n2. **`TranscriptAnalyzer`** - For format-specific transcript parsing\\n   - `GetTranscriptPosition()` - Current line/message count\\n   - `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset()` - Files modified since offset\\n\\n3. **`TokenCalculator`** - For token usage calculation\\n   - `CalculateTokenUsage()` - Compute tokens from transcript\\n\\n4. **`TranscriptPreparer`** - For async transcript sync (Claude Code)\\n   - `PrepareTranscript()` - Flush/sync before reading\\n\\n5. **`TextGenerator`** - For non-interactive text generation\\n   - `GenerateText()` - Send prompt to agent CLI\\n\\n6. **`HookResponseWriter`** - For structured hook responses\\n   - `WriteHookResponse()` - Output messages via agent protocol\\n\\n7. **`SubagentAwareExtractor`** - For subagent support\\n   - `ExtractAllModifiedFiles()` - Including subagents\\n   - `CalculateTotalTokenUsage()` - Including subagents\\n\\n8. **`TestOnly`** - For test agents (Vogon)\\n   - `IsTestOnly()` - Marker interface\\n\\n**Agent Registry (`registry.go`):**\\n\\n```go\\n// Global registry (thread-safe with RWMutex)\\nvar registry = make(map[types.AgentName]Factory)\\n\\n// Factory function type\\ntype Factory func() Agent\\n\\n// Register adds an agent factory to registry\\nfunc Register(name types.AgentName, factory Factory)\\n\\n// Get retrieves an agent by name\\nfunc Get(name types.AgentName) (Agent, error)\\n\\n// List returns all registered agent names (sorted)\\nfunc List() []types.AgentName\\n\\n// Detect auto-detects which agent is being used\\nfunc Detect(ctx context.Context) (Agent, error)\\n\\n// DetectAll returns all agents whose DetectPresence reports true\\nfunc DetectAll(ctx context.Context) []Agent\\n```\\n\\n**Agent Name and Type Constants:**\\n\\n```go\\n// Registry keys (agent names)\\nconst (\\n    AgentNameClaudeCode     = \\\"claude-code\\\"\\n    AgentNameCopilotCLI     = \\\"copilot-cli\\\"\\n    AgentNameCursor         = \\\"cursor\\\"\\n    AgentNameFactoryAIDroid = \\\"factoryai-droid\\\"\\n    AgentNameGemini         = \\\"gemini\\\"\\n    AgentNameOpenCode       = \\\"opencode\\\"\\n)\\n\\n// Type identifiers (stored in metadata)\\nconst (\\n    AgentTypeClaudeCode     = \\\"Claude Code\\\"\\n    AgentTypeCopilotCLI     = \\\"Copilot CLI\\\"\\n    AgentTypeCursor         = \\\"Cursor\\\"\\n    AgentTypeFactoryAIDroid = \\\"Factory AI Droid\\\"\\n    AgentTypeGemini         = \\\"Gemini CLI\\\"\\n    AgentTypeOpenCode       = \\\"OpenCode\\\"\\n    AgentTypeUnknown        = \\\"Agent\\\"\\n)\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. SHADOW BRANCH CREATION\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go`\\n\\n**Shadow Branch Design:**\\n\\nShadow branches are ephemeral branches used to store checkpoint data before condensation to permanent storage.\\n\\n**Naming Convention:**\\n```\\nentire/<commit-hash[:7]>-<worktree-hash[:6]>\\n```\\n\\nExample: `entire/abc1234-def567`\\n\\n**Structure:**\\n- **Prefix:** `entire/` (constant `ShadowBranchPrefix`)\\n- **Commit hash:** First 7 hex chars of base commit (constant `ShadowBranchHashLength = 7`)\\n- **Separator:** Single dash `-`\\n- **Worktree hash:** 6-char hex hash of worktree path (prevents conflicts across git worktrees)\\n\\n**Shadow Branch Functions:**\\n\\n1. **`ShadowBranchNameForCommit(baseCommit, worktreeID string) string`**\\n   - Takes full commit hash and worktree ID\\n   - Returns formatted shadow branch name\\n   - Example: `ShadowBranchNameForCommit(\\\"abc1234567890def\\\", \\\"worktree-path\\\")` → `entire/abc1234-<hash>`\\n\\n2. **`ParseShadowBranchName(branchName string) (commitPrefix, worktreeHash string, ok bool)`**\\n   - Extracts commit prefix and worktree hash from shadow branch name\\n   - Returns `(commitPrefix, worktreeHash, true)` if valid shadow branch\\n   - Returns `(\\\"\\\", \\\"\\\", false)` if not a shadow branch\\n   - Handles legacy format without worktree hash (returns with empty worktreeHash)\\n\\n3. **`getOrCreateShadowBranch(branchName string) (parentHash, baseTreeHash, error)`**\\n   - Gets or creates a shadow branch\\n   - If branch exists: returns current commit and tree hash\\n   - If branch doesn't exist: creates it based on HEAD's tree\\n\\n**Worktree ID Hashing:**\\n\\nThe `HashWorktreeID()` function (likely in a utility module) creates a 6-char hash of the worktree path to ensure:\\n- Different git worktrees have separate shadow branches\\n- Main worktree (empty ID) gets consistent hash\\n- Prevents checkpoint conflicts when using git worktrees\\n\\n**Shadow Branch Usage in Checkpoints:**\\n\\n1. **WriteTemporary()** creates/updates shadow branch commits\\n   - Gets or creates shadow branch via `getOrCreateShadowBranch()`\\n   - Deduplicates checkpoints by comparing tree hashes\\n   - Creates commit with metadata (session ID, metadata dir, trailers)\\n   - Updates branch reference to point to new commit\\n\\n2. **Shadow branches persist during session lifecycle:**\\n   - Created on first `SaveStep()`\\n   - Additional commits added for subsequent steps\\n   - Cleaned up or migrated when base commit changes (pull/rebase)\\n   - Eventually condensed to permanent storage on git commit\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. CHECKPOINT CONDENSATION\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`\\n\\n**Condensation Process:**\\n\\nCondensation moves session data from ephemeral shadow branches to permanent storage on the `entire/checkpoints/v1` metadata branch.\\n\\n**Key Functions:**\\n\\n1. **`listCheckpoints(ctx context.Context) ([]CheckpointInfo, error)`**\\n   - Lists all checkpoints from metadata branch\\n   - Uses `checkpoint.GitStore.ListCommitted()`\\n   - Returns metadata including checkpoint ID, session ID, created date, files touched, agent\\n\\n2. **`getCheckpointLog(ctx context.Context, checkpointID id.CheckpointID) ([]byte, error)`**\\n   - Retrieves transcript for a specific checkpoint ID\\n   - Uses `store.ReadLatestSessionContent()`\\n   - Reads from `entire/checkpoints/v1` metadata branch\\n\\n3. **`CondenseSession(ctx context.Context, repo *git.Repository, checkpointID id.CheckpointID, state *SessionState, committedFiles map[string]struct{}, opts ...condenseOpts) (*CondenseResult, error)`**\\n\\nThis is the main condensation function:\\n\\n**Input parameters:**\\n- `checkpointID` - 12-hex-char stable identifier from Entire-Checkpoint trailer\\n- `state` - SessionState containing checkpoint metadata\\n- `committedFiles` - Files actually committed (for 1:1 checkpoint model)\\n- `opts` - Pre-resolved git objects (optimization)\\n\\n**Process:**\\n1. Gets shadow branch (or uses live transcript if shadow branch missing)\\n2. Extracts session data via `extractSessionData()`:\\n   - Reads full transcript\\n   - Extracts prompts\\n   - Collects files touched\\n   - Calculates token usage\\n3. Filters files to only those actually committed (1:1 checkpoint model)\\n4. Calculates attribution (user vs agent line changes)\\n5. Generates summary if enabled (`settings.IsSummarizeEnabled()`)\\n6. Writes to metadata branch via `store.WriteCommitted()`\\n7. Returns `CondenseResult` with checkpoint info\\n\\n**Metadata Storage:**\\n\\nCheckpoints are stored on the `entire/checkpoints/v1` orphan branch with sharded directory structure:\\n\\n```\\n<checkpoint-id[:2]>/<checkpoint-id[2:]>/\\n├── metadata.json              # CheckpointSummary\\n├── 0/                         # Session 0 (first session)\\n│   ├── metadata.json          # Session-specific metadata\\n│   ├── full.jsonl             # Complete transcript\\n│   ├── prompt.txt             # User prompts\\n│   ├── content_hash.txt       # SHA256 of transcript\\n│   └── tasks/<tool-use-id>/   # Task checkpoints\\n│       ├── checkpoint.json    # UUID mapping\\n│       └── agent-<id>.jsonl   # Subagent transcript\\n├── 1/                         # Session 1 (if multi-session)\\n└── ...\\n```\\n\\n**Multi-Session Condensation:**\\n\\nWhen multiple sessions condense to the same checkpoint (same base commit):\\n- Sessions stored in numbered folders (0, 1, 2, ...)\\n- Latest session always in highest-numbered folder\\n- `metadata.json` contains:\\n  - `session_id` - Latest/current session\\n  - `session_ids` - All session IDs\\n  - `session_count` - Number of sessions\\n  - `files_touched` - Merged from all sessions\\n\\n**Attribution Calculation:**\\n\\n`calculateSessionAttributions()` determines user vs agent contributions by:\\n1. Comparing trees between base commit and agent's work\\n2. Identifying user edits made before the session\\n3. Counting added/removed lines per file\\n4. Stores attribution data for trail display\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. SESSION STATE MANAGEMENT\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/session_state.go` and `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/session/`\\n\\n**Session State Persistence:**\\n\\nSession state is stored in `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` files (shared across worktrees):\\n\\n```go\\ntype SessionState struct {\\n    // Core identifiers\\n    SessionID      string\\n    BaseCommit     string  // HEAD commit when session started\\n    WorktreeID     string  // Git worktree identifier\\n    WorktreePath   string  // Absolute path to worktree\\n    \\n    // Session phase (ACTIVE, IDLE, ENDED)\\n    Phase          session.Phase\\n    \\n    // Checkpoint tracking\\n    StepCount           int              // Number of checkpoints saved\\n    LastCheckpointID    id.CheckpointID  // 12-hex ID from last condensation\\n    FilesTouched        []string         // Accumulated files touched\\n    CheckpointTranscriptStart int        // Starting message index\\n    \\n    // Agent/model info\\n    AgentType      types.AgentType\\n    ModelName      string\\n    TranscriptPath string\\n    \\n    // Prompts and attribution\\n    LastPrompt              string\\n    PromptAttributions      []session.PromptAttribution\\n    PendingPromptAttribution *session.PromptAttribution\\n    \\n    // Timestamps\\n    StartedAt            time.Time\\n    LastInteractionTime  *time.Time\\n    \\n    // Token usage accumulation\\n    TokenUsage           *agent.TokenUsage\\n    \\n    // Other metadata\\n    TurnID              string\\n    CLIVersion          string\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**State Lifecycle:**\\n\\n1. **InitializeSession()** - Called on first user prompt\\n   - Creates new SessionState with current HEAD as BaseCommit\\n   - Sets phase to ACTIVE\\n   - Generates TurnID for this turn\\n\\n2. **UpdateSessionState()** - Called during SaveStep()\\n   - Increments StepCount\\n   - Appends PromptAttributions\\n   - Merges FilesTouched\\n   - Accumulates TokenUsage\\n\\n3. **CondenseSession()** - Called on git commit\\n   - Reads session state\\n   - Extracts session data from shadow branch\\n   - Calculates attribution\\n   - Writes to metadata branch\\n   - Sets LastCheckpointID\\n\\n4. **TransitionAndLog()** - Called to change phase\\n   - Handles events (TurnStart, TurnEnd, SessionStart, SessionStop)\\n   - Transitions: IDLE ↔ ACTIVE, ENDED\\n   - Triggers condensation on certain transitions\\n\\n**Session Discovery:**\\n\\n```go\\n// LoadSessionState - Load specific session\\nfunc LoadSessionState(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SessionState, error)\\n\\n// ListSessionStates - List all active sessions\\nfunc ListSessionStates(ctx context.Context) ([]*SessionState, error)\\n\\n// FindMostRecentSession - Get most recently interacted session ID\\nfunc FindMostRecentSession(ctx context.Context) string\\n\\n// SaveSessionState - Persist session state atomically\\nfunc SaveSessionState(ctx context.Context, state *SessionState) error\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 7. INITIALIZATION AND SESSION ATTACHMENT FLOW\\n\\n**How InitializeSession Works:**\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) InitializeSession(\\n    ctx context.Context,\\n    sessionID string,\\n    agentType types.AgentType,\\n    transcriptPath string,\\n    userPrompt string,\\n    model string,\\n) error\\n```\\n\\n**For existing sessions (resuming):**\\n1. Loads existing session state\\n2. Applies phase transition (IDLE/ENDED → ACTIVE)\\n3. Generates new TurnID for this turn\\n4. Updates ModelName if provided\\n5. Updates LastPrompt\\n6. Clears LastCheckpointID (set during PostCommit)\\n7. Calculates prompt attribution at start (user edits before this turn