oadSessionState(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SessionState, error)\\n\\n// ListSessionStates - List all active sessions\\nfunc ListSessionStates(ctx context.Context) ([]*SessionState, error)\\n\\n// FindMostRecentSession - Get most recently interacted session ID\\nfunc FindMostRecentSession(ctx context.Context) string\\n\\n// SaveSessionState - Persist session state atomically\\nfunc SaveSessionState(ctx context.Context, state *SessionState) error\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 7. INITIALIZATION AND SESSION ATTACHMENT FLOW\\n\\n**How InitializeSession Works:**\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) InitializeSession(\\n    ctx context.Context,\\n    sessionID string,\\n    agentType types.AgentType,\\n    transcriptPath string,\\n    userPrompt string,\\n    model string,\\n) error\\n```\\n\\n**For existing sessions (resuming):**\\n1. Loads existing session state\\n2. Applies phase transition (IDLE/ENDED → ACTIVE)\\n3. Generates new TurnID for this turn\\n4. Updates ModelName if provided\\n5. Updates LastPrompt\\n6. Clears LastCheckpointID (set during PostCommit)\\n7. Calculates prompt attribution at start (user edits before this turn)\\n8. Checks if HEAD changed (shadow branch migration)\\n9. Saves updated state\\n\\n**For new sessions (attach command):**\\n1. Calls internal `initializeSession()` to create new SessionState\\n2. Sets BaseCommit to current HEAD\\n3. Sets WorktreeID from current git worktree\\n4. Applies phase transition (new → ACTIVE)\\n5. Calculates prompt attribution for pre-prompt user edits\\n6. Saves state\\n\\n**Then SaveStep() is called to create the shadow branch checkpoint:**\\n1. Opens git repository\\n2. Loads session state\\n3. Migrates shadow branch if needed\\n4. Calls `store.WriteTemporary()` to create checkpoint commit\\n5. Updates session state (StepCount, FilesTouched, TokenUsage)\\n6. Saves updated state\\n\\n**Finally CondenseSessionByID() condenses to permanent storage:**\\n1. Loads session state\\n2. Extracts session da