 `InitializeSession()` → `SaveStep()` → `CondenseSession()` but skips the full `TurnStart`/`TurnEnd` lifecycle that populates intermediate state. The gaps:\\n\\n| Gap | Impact |\\n|-----|--------|\\n| **No `prompt.txt` written to metadata dir** | Condensation finds no prompts → UI can't render checkpoint |\\n| **No token usage calculation** | `token_usage` empty or minimal |\\n| **No session metrics** | Missing `turn_count`, `duration_ms`, etc. |\\n| **`extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` only parses JSONL** | Gemini transcripts (`{\\\"messages\\\":[...]}`) won't extract prompts |\\n| **No model extraction from transcript** | `ModelName` stays empty |\\n| **No prompt attribution** | `initial_attribution` shows zeros |\\n\\nThe **`prompt.txt` gap is the blocker** — the UI requires it to display the checkpoint. The others are data quality issues.\\n\\nDoes this match your understanding so far?\\n\\n### Section 2: Proposed Fix\\n\\nAll changes in `attach.go` — no strategy/checkpoint changes needed since the underlying pipeline works correctly when given complete data.\\n\\n**Fix 1: Write `prompt.txt` before `SaveStep`**\\nAfter extracting `firstPrompt` (line 169), write it to the metadata dir:\\n```go\\nif firstPrompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    promptFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.PromptFileName)\\n    os.WriteFile(promptFile, []byte(firstPrompt), 0o600)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Fix 2: Extract prompts from Gemini transcripts**\\n`extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` currently only uses `transcript.ParseFromBytes` (JSONL). Add a fallback that parses Gemini's `{\\\"messages\\\":[...]}` format, looking for `\\\"type\\\":\\\"human\\\"` messages.\\n\\n**Fix 3: Calculate token usage before SaveStep**\\nIf the agent implements `TokenCalculator`, call `CalculateTokenUsage(transcriptData, 0)` and pass the result into the session state before `SaveStep`.\\n\\n**Fix 4: Extract model name from transcript**\\nFor Claude Code, parse the transcript for model info. For Gemini, extract from the `beforeModel` hook data or message metadata. Store in `state.ModelName`.\\n\\n**Fix 5: Set session metrics from transcript analysis**\\nCount turns in the transcript (user messages = turns). Set `SessionTurnCount` on the state. Duration can be estimated from first/last message timestamps if available.\\n\\n**Fix 6: Attribution calculation**\\nThe attach flow already calls `InitializeSession` which calculates `PendingPromptAttribution`. The gap is that `SaveStep` needs the attribution data populated. Since attach represents a single \\\"turn\\\" covering the whole session, the attribution should reflect all file changes as agent-authored.\\n\\nDoes this design look right? Any concerns before I write the spec?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4220,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":105094,\"output_tokens\":721,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":4220,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYyqN5W61tDc5gSJK4nom\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"da29243a-89b1-4b99-9751-446154b4cd1e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:42:00.131Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"61b0a478-d835-45a6-936a-9d30f7ba786c\",\"version\":\"2.1.74\",\"gitBranch\":\"attach-session-id\",\"slug\":\"fancy-dreaming-biscuit\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"da29243a-89b1-4b99-9751-446154b4cd1e\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"ee409c97-fc9a-458a-bfd4-8a9672015272\",\"toolUseID\":\"ee409c97-fc9a-458a-bfd4-8a9672015272\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:42:00.154Z\",\"uuid\":\"3051cd71-efe5-4