ow calls `InitializeSession()` → `SaveStep()` → `CondenseSession()` but skips the intermediate lifecycle steps that populate session state and write artifacts like `prompt.txt`.\\n\\n## Observed Gaps\\n\\n| Data Item | Hook Flow | Attach Flow | Impact |\\n|-----------|-----------|-------------|--------|\\n| `prompt.txt` in metadata dir | Written by TurnStart handler | **Not written** | UI cannot render checkpoint (blocker) |\\n| Prompt extraction for Gemini | N/A (hooks provide prompt) | `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` only parses JSONL | Gemini sessions get empty prompts |\\n| Token usage | `CalculateTokenUsage()` called in TurnEnd | **Not calculated** | Empty `token_usage` in metadata |\\n| Model name | Provided by hook events | **Not extracted** | Empty `model` field in metadata |\\n| Session metrics (turn_count, duration) | `persistEventMetadataToState()` in PostCommit | **Not set** | Missing `session_metrics` in metadata |\\n\\n## Constraints\\n\\n- **Do not alter existing strategy, checkpoint, or lifecycle logic.** All fixes are scoped to `attach.go` and supporting helpers.\\n- The existing pipeline (SaveStep → CondenseSession → WriteCommitted) works correctly when given complete input data. The fix is to ensure attach provides complete data.\\n- Must work for all registered agents: claude-code, gemini, opencode, cursor, copilot-cli, factoryai-droid.\\n\\n## Design\\n\\n### Fix 1: Write `prompt.txt` to metadata dir before SaveStep\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n\\nAfter extracting `firstPrompt` (line 169) and creating the metadata directory (line 154), write the prompt file:\\n\\n```go\\nif firstPrompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    promptFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.PromptFileName)\\n    if err := os.WriteFile(promptFile, []byte(firstPrompt), 0o600); err != nil {\\n        logging.Warn(logCtx, \\\"failed to write prompt file\\\", \\\"error\\\", err)\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis ensures `SaveStep` picks up `prompt.txt` when copying the metadata dir to the shadow branch, and `CondenseSession` finds it when extracting session data.\\n\\n### Fix 2: Extract prompts from Gemini transcripts\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` (modify `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript`)\\n\\nThe current implementation only uses `transcript.ParseFromBytes()` which parses JSONL (Claude Code format). Add a fallback for Gemini's JSON format:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc extractFirstPromptFromTranscript(data []byte) string {\\n    // Try JSONL format first (Claude Code, OpenCode, etc.)\\n    lines, err := transcript.ParseFromBytes(data)\\n    if err == nil {\\n        for _, line := range lines {\\n            if line.Type == transcript.TypeUser {\\n                if prompt := extractTextFromMessage(line.Message); prompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n                    return prompt\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    // Fallback: try Gemini JSON format {\\\"messages\\\": [...]}\\n    return extractFirstPromptFromGeminiTranscript(data)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nNew helper `extractFirstPromptFromGeminiTranscript`:\\n- Parse as `{\\\"messages\\\": [...]}`\\n- Find first message with `\\\"type\\\": \\\"human\\\"` (Gemini's user message type)\\n- Extract text content from the message parts\\n\\n### Fix 3: Calculate token usage\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n\\nAfter reading the transcript, if the agent implements `TokenCalculator`, calculate usage:\\n\\n```go\\nif calc, ok := agent.AsTokenCalculator(ag); ok {\\n    if usage, err := calc.CalculateTokenUsage(transcriptData, 0); err == nil && usage != nil {\\n        state.TokenUsage = usage\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis must happen after `InitializeSession` and before `SaveStep`, updating the session state so that `CondenseSession` picks it up.\\n\\n### Fix 4: Extract model name from transcript\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n\\nAdd a helper that extracts the model name from the transcript:\\n- **Claude Code:** Look for `\\\"model\\\"` field in assistant messages\\n- **Gemini:** Look for model info in message metadata or `beforeModel` hook data\\n\\nSet `state.ModelName` before `SaveStep`.\\n\\n### Fix 5: Set session metrics from transcript\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n\\nCount user messages in the transcript to determine turn count. Estimate duration from first/last message timestamps if available:\\n\\n```go\\nstate.SessionTurnCount = countUserTurns(transcriptData, ag)\\nif firstTS, lastTS := extractTimestampRange(transcriptData); !firstTS.IsZero() {\\n    state.SessionDurationMs = int64(lastTS.Sub(firstTS).Milliseconds())\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Fix 6: Ensure attribution populates correctly\\n\\n`InitializeSession()` already calculates `PendingPromptAttribution` (comparing working tree state against HEAD). This flows through `SaveStep` into the session state's `PromptAttributions` array, which `CondenseSession` uses for `initial_attribution`.\\n\\nVerify this works correctly for attach by ensuring `SaveStep` receives the full file change list. The current code already passes `relModifiedFiles`, `relNewFiles`, and `relDeletedFiles` to `StepContext` — no change needed here, just verification via tests.\\n\\n## File Changes Summary\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` | Write `prompt.txt`, calculate token usage, extract model, set session metrics |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` | Update `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` to handle Gemini format |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/attach_test.go` | Tests for all new behavior |\\n\\n## Testing\\n\\n- Unit tests: `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` with Claude Code JSONL and Gemini JSON transcripts\\n- Unit tests: token usage, model extraction, session metrics for both transcript formats\\n- Integration test: full attach flow produces checkpoint with `prompt.txt`, populated token usage, session metrics, and attribution\\n- E2E canary (Vogon): if attach is exercised in E2E tests, verify checkpoint data completeness\\n- Manual verification: `entire attach <gemini-session-id> --agent gemini` produces a checkpoint visible in UI\\n\\n## Out of Scope\\n\\n- Changes to strategy, checkpoint, or lifecycle code\\n- Changes to the push flow (pre-push hook already works correctly)\\n- UI changes\\n- New agent implementations\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":112,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":110386,\"output_tokens\":1815,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":112,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYyqW5TaWRGmS5pc1MydV\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"070b8a68-5300-4969-a63c-8b91f7fe4f00\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:44:04.218Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"61b0a478-d835-45a6-936a-9d30f7ba786c\",\"version\":\"2.1.74\",\"gitBranch\":\"attach-session-id\",\"slug\":\"fancy-dreaming-biscuit\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"070b8a68-5300-4969-a63c-8b91f7fe4f00\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Write\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01GTBB567M1tPaJJhSArBeuG\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01GTBB567M1tPaJJhSArBeuG\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:44:04.246Z\",\"uuid\":\"2c1c30e8-3c8e-4ccb-8661-5b88d1158f74\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"61b0a478-d835-45a6-936a-9d30f7ba786c\",\"version\":\"2.1.74\",\"gitBranch\":\"attach-session-id\",\"slug\":\"fancy-dreaming-biscuit\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"070b8a68-5300-4969-a63c-8b91f7fe4f00\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"promptId\":\"1bcf6f67-c204-4879-a1b8-5b9dd4cfb482\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"to