ty `token_usage` in metadata |\\n    20→| Model name | Provided by hook events | **Not extracted** | Empty `model` field in metadata |\\n    21→| Session metrics (turn_count, duration) | `persistEventMetadataToState()` in PostCommit | **Not set** | Missing `session_metrics` in metadata |\\n    22→\\n    23→## Constraints\\n    24→\\n    25→- **Do not alter existing strategy, checkpoint, or lifecycle logic.** All fixes are scoped to `attach.go` and supporting helpers.\\n    26→- The existing pipeline (SaveStep → CondenseSession → WriteCommitted) works correctly when given complete input data. The fix is to ensure attach provides complete data.\\n    27→- Must work for all registered agents: claude-code, gemini, opencode, cursor, copilot-cli, factoryai-droid.\\n    28→\\n    29→## Design\\n    30→\\n    31→### Fix 1: Write `prompt.txt` to metadata dir before SaveStep\\n    32→\\n    33→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n    34→\\n    35→After extracting `firstPrompt` (line 169) and creating the metadata directory (line 154), write the prompt file:\\n    36→\\n    37→```go\\n    38→if firstPrompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    39→    promptFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.PromptFileName)\\n    40→    if err := os.WriteFile(promptFile, []byte(firstPrompt), 0o600); err != nil {\\n    41→        logging.Warn(logCtx, \\\"failed to write prompt file\\\", \\\"error\\\", err)\\n    42→    }\\n    43→}\\n    44→```\\n    45→\\n    46→This ensures `SaveStep` picks up `prompt.txt` when copying the metadata dir to the shadow branch, and `CondenseSession` finds it when extracting session data.\\n    47→\\n    48→### Fix 2: Extract prompts from Gemini transcripts\\n    49→\\n    50→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` (modify `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript`)\\n    51→\\n    52→The current implementation only uses `transcript.ParseFromBytes()` which parses JSONL (Claude Code format). Add a fallback for Gemini's JSON format:\\n    53→\\n    54→```go\\n    55→func extractFirstPromptFromTranscript(data []byte) string {\\n    56→    // Try JSONL format first (Claude Code, OpenCode, etc.)\\n    57→    lines, err := transcript.ParseFromBytes(data)\\n    58→    if err == nil {\\n    59→        for _, line := range lines {\\n    60→            if line.Type == transcript.TypeUser {\\n    61→                if prompt := extractTextFromMessage(line.Message); prompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    62→                    return prompt\\n    63→                }\\n    64→            }\\n    65→        }\\n    66→    }\\n    67→\\n    68→    // Fallback: try Gemini JSON format {\\\"messages\\\": [...]}\\n    69→    return extractFirstPromptFromGeminiTranscript(data)\\n    70→}\\n    71→```\\n    72→\\n    73→New helper `extractFirstPromptFromGeminiTranscript`:\\n    74→- Parse as `{\\\"messages\\\": [...]}`\\n    75→- Find first message with `\\\"type\\\": \\\"human\\\"` (Gemini's user message type)\\n    76→- Extract text content from the message parts\\n    77→\\n    78→### Fix 3: Calculate token usage\\n    79→\\n    80→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n    81→\\n    82→After reading the transcript, if the agent implements `TokenCalculator`, calculate usage:\\n    83→\\n    84→```go\\n    85→if calc, ok := agent.AsTokenCalculator(ag); ok {\\n    86→    if usage, err := calc.CalculateTokenUsage(transcriptData, 0); err == nil && usage != nil {\\n    87→        state.TokenUsage = usage\\n    88→    }\\n    89→}\\n    90→```\\n    91→\\n    92→This must happen after `InitializeSession` and before `SaveStep`, updating the session state so that `CondenseSession` picks it up.\\n    93→\\n    94→### Fix 4: Extract model name from transcript\\n    95→\\n    96→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n    97→\\n    98→Add a helper that extracts the model name from the transcript:\\n    99→- **Claude Code:** Look for `\\\"model\\\"` field in assistant messages\\n   100→- **Gemini:** Look for model info in message metadata or `beforeModel` hook data\\n   101→\\n   102→Set `state.ModelName` before `SaveStep`.\\n   103→\\n   104→### Fix 5: Set session metrics from transcript\\n   105→\\n   106→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n   107→\\n   108→Count user messages in the transcript to determine turn count. Estimate duration from first/last message timestamps if available:\\n   109→\\n   110→```go\\n   111→state.SessionTurnCount = countUserTurns(transcriptData, ag)\\n   112→if firstTS, lastTS := extractTimestampRange(transcriptData); !firstTS.IsZero() {\\n   113→    state.SessionDurationMs = int64(lastTS.Sub(firstTS).Milliseconds())\\n   114→}\\n   115→```\\n   116→\\n   117→### Fix 6: Ensure attribution populates correctly\\n   118→\\n   119→`InitializeSession()` already calculates `PendingPromptAttribution` (comparing working tree state against HEAD). This flows through `SaveStep` into the session state's `PromptAttributions` array, which `CondenseSession` uses for `initial_attribution`.\\n   120→\\n   121→Verify this works correctly for attach by ensuring `SaveStep` receives the full file change list. The current code already passes `relModifiedFiles`, `relNewFiles`, and `relDeletedFiles` to `StepContext` — no change needed here, just verification via tests.\\n   122→\\n   123→## File Changes Summary\\n   124→\\n   125→| File | Change |\\n   126→|------|--------|\\n   127→| `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` | Write `prompt.txt`, calculate token usage, extract model, set session metrics |\\n   128→| `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` | Update `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` to handle Gemini format |\\n   129→| `cmd/entire/cli/attach_test.go` | Tests for all new behavior |\\n   130→\\n   131→## Testing\\n   132→\\n   133→- Unit tests: `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` with Claude Code JSONL and Gemini JSON transcripts\\n   134→- Unit tests: token usage, model extraction, session metrics for both transcript formats\\n   135→- Integration test: full attach flow produces checkpoint with `prompt.txt`, populated token usage, session metrics, and attribution\\n   136→- E2E canary (Vogon): if attach is exercised in E2E tests, verify checkpoint data completeness\\n   137→- Manual verification: `entire attach <gemini-session-id> --agent gemini` produces a checkpoint visible in UI\\n   138→\\n   139→## Out of Scope\\n   140→\\n   141→- Changes to strategy, checkpoint, or lifecycle code\\n   142→- Changes to the push flow (pre-push hook already works correctly)\\n   143→- UI changes\\n   144→- New agent implementations\\n   145→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"db7e86fc-4360-4c04-85f4-a0e7eebbe29c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:44:17.868Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a8f789aafdc6eb9cc\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01WGyfbFu9aawLjJuKhd3AgC\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_012k3WR2wzXJaekTkrEUpB8M\",\"uuid\":\"088018bf-525a-4132-96ed-bf773b331a8a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:44:17.869Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"61b0a478-d835-45a6-936a-9d30f7ba786c\",\"version\":\"2.1.74\",\"gitBranch\":\"attach-session-id\",\"slug\":\"fancy-dreaming-biscuit\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"088018bf-525a-4132-96ed-bf773b331a8a\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:44:18.384Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01UCUtzyMb6hnnKfrofusbNc\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01MC3DF6cys7eyBEZCgVuusg\",\"name\":\"Glob\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/**/types.go\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":17374,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":17374,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYyqZMwrPGuWgkMRddQAo\",\"uui