\\n   496→\\t}\\n   497→\\n   498→\\t// Use tracked files from session state (not all files in tree)\\n   499→\\tdata.FilesTouched = filesTouched\\n   500→\\n   501→\\t// Calculate token usage from the extracted transcript portion\\n   502→\\tif len(data.Transcript) > 0 {\\n   503→\\t\\tdata.TokenUsage = agent.CalculateTokenUsage(ctx, ag, data.Transcript, checkpointTranscriptStart, \\\"\\\") //TODO: why do we not use here subagents dir?\\n   504→\\t}\\n   505→\\n   506→\\treturn data, nil\\n   507→}\\n   508→\\n   509→// extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript extracts session data directly from the live transcript file.\\n   510→// This is used for mid-session commits where no shadow branch exists yet.\\n   511→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript(ctx context.Context, state *SessionState) (*ExtractedSessionData, error) {\\n   512→\\tdata := &ExtractedSessionData{}\\n   513→\\n   514→\\tag, _ := agent.GetByAgentType(state.AgentType) //nolint:errcheck // ag may be nil for unknown agent types; callers use type assertions so nil is safe\\n   515→\\n   516→\\t// Read the live transcript\\n   517→\\tif state.TranscriptPath == \\\"\\\" {\"}]},\"uuid\":\"6374f081-bbf4-4178-9d11-b3b2f9c659af\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:45:49.662Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a8f789aafdc6eb9cc\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01WGyfbFu9aawLjJuKhd3AgC\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_012k3WR2wzXJaekTkrEUpB8M\",\"uuid\":\"92e9b462-75b7-4acb-9db8-a4078c8324a4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:45:49.672Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"61b0a478-d835-45a6-936a-9d30f7ba786c\",\"version\":\"2.1.74\",\"gitBranch\":\"attach-session-id\",\"slug\":\"fancy-dreaming-biscuit\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"92e9b462-75b7-4acb-9db8-a4078c8324a4\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:46:40.121Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01PatTgaNB7QrPpV8U71JAc2\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01TVLkU9nDH9B1sN6QRuF4eK\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/docs/superpowers/specs/review-01.md\",\"content\":\"# Review 01\\n\\n> Status: pending-dev\\n> Date: 2026-03-12\\n> Reviewer: Code Review Agent\\n> Verdict: REQUEST CHANGES\\n\\n## Previous Review Status\\n\\nNo previous reviews.\\n\\n## New Findings\\n\\n### Critical (Must Fix)\\n\\n- **[Spec, Fix 2]** Gemini transcript uses `\\\"type\\\": \\\"user\\\"`, NOT `\\\"type\\\": \\\"human\\\"`. The spec states the fallback should look for `\\\"type\\\": \\\"human\\\"` but the actual Gemini transcript format uses `MessageTypeUser = \\\"user\\\"` (defined at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/transcript.go:15`). The `GeminiMessage.Type` field uses constants `\\\"user\\\"` and `\\\"gemini\\\"`. The spec must be corrected, AND there is already a function `ExtractAllUserPrompts` / `ExtractAllUserPromptsFromTranscript` in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/transcript.go:154-173` that does exactly what the spec proposes. The new helper `extractFirstPromptFromGeminiTranscript` should reuse this existing function rather than re-implementing the parsing.\\n\\n- **[Spec, Fix 3]** The code sample `agent.AsTokenCalculator(ag)` returns a `(TokenCalculator, bool)`, but the spec then calls `calc.CalculateTokenUsage(transcriptData, 0)`. This is correct for the interface signature (`CalculateTokenUsage(transcriptData []byte, fromOffset int) (*TokenUsage, error)`), however the spec ignores the higher-level `agent.CalculateTokenUsage()` function at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/token_usage.go:13` which also checks for `SubagentAwareExtractor` first and handles errors with logging. The attach flow should use this higher-level function instead for consistency with the hook flow and to get subagent token data for free:\\n  ```go\\n  usage := agent.CalculateTokenUsage(ctx, ag, transcriptData, 0, \\\"\\\")\\n  if usage != nil {\\n      state.TokenUsage = usage\\n  }\\n  ```\\n\\n- **[Spec, Fix 3]** The spec says to set `state.TokenUsage` before `SaveStep`, but the condensation flow at `manual_commit_condensation.go:151-152` recalculates token usage from the transcript and overwrites `state.TokenUsage` when `InputTokens > 0`. This means setting it on the session state before SaveStep may be partially redundant since condensation re-extracts it. However, if condensation fails (fallback to shadow branch only), token data would be lost. The spec should clarify this dual-path behavior and confirm the intent is to populate the state as a safety net.\\n\\n### Important (Should Fix)\\n\\n- **[Spec, Fix 5]** The proposed `countUserTurns` and `extractTimestampRange` helpers are underspecified. The hook flow calculates `SessionTurnCount` by incrementing on each `TurnEnd` event or using agent-reported `event.TurnCount` (see `lifecycle.go:836-842`). For the attach flow with a single transcript, counting user messages is a reasonable proxy, but the spec should note that this produces a different semantic than the hook flow (which counts completed turns). For Gemini, timestamps are not part of the `GeminiMessage` struct at all (see `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/transcript.go:25-29` -- no timestamp field), so `extractTimestampRange` would always return zero for Gemini. The spec should acknowledge this limitation.\\n\\n- **[Spec, Fix 1]** The code uses `paths.PromptFileName` which does exist (`cmd/entire/cli/paths/paths.go:25`, value `\\\"prompt.txt\\\"`), but the spec should note that `prompt.txt` written to the metadata directory must be in the correct format. Looking at the condensation flow in `extractSessionData` at `manual_commit_condensation.go:487-489`, it reads `prompt.txt` from the shadow branch tree and calls `splitPromptContent()`. The spec should clarify that `firstPrompt` should be written as-is (single prompt, no delimiter needed) since this is a single-prompt attach, and confirm `splitPromptContent` handles single-line content correctly.\\n\\n- **[Spec, Fix 4]** Model name extraction from transcripts is vague. For Claude Code, the model is in JSONL assistant message fields. For Gemini, model info comes from `BeforeModel` hooks (see `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/types.go:66-74`), not from the transcript itself -- the `GeminiMessage` struct has no model field. The spec should either acknowledge that model extraction from Gemini transcripts is not feasible (and skip it), or specify a concrete approach. Currently in the hook flow, the Gemini model is captured via `BeforeModel` hook data, which would not be available in the attach flow.\\n\\n- **[Spec, General]** The spec does not address `state.LastPrompt` population. In the hook flow, `LastPrompt` is set via `truncatePromptForStorage(prompt)` during turn start. The attach flow calls `InitializeSession` which likely handles this, but it should be verified and documented. `InitializeSession` receives `firstPrompt` as a parameter.\\n\\n### Suggestions (Consider)\\n\\n- **[Spec, Fix 2]** Rather than adding a Gemini-specific fallback inside `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript`, consider using the agent interface to dispatch. Each agent already knows how to parse its own transcript format. A cleaner approach might be to add an optional `PromptExtractor` interface or to use the existing `ExtractAllUserPrompts` from the Gemini agent directly, keyed by agent type. This avoids `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` needing to know about every transcript format.\\n\\n- **[Spec, Fix 5]** For `SessionDurationMs`, Claude Code transcripts do have timestamps in their JSONL entries. Consider extracting duration only for agents whose transcripts include timestamps, and documenting which agents will have this data populated vs. left at zero.\\n\\n- **[Spec, Testing]** The testing section should specify that the integration test must verify `prompt.txt` content survives the full `SaveStep -> CondenseSession -> WriteCommitted` pipeline and appears in the committed checkpoint tree. A unit test for just writing the file is insufficient to verify end-to-end correctness.\\n\\n### Praise\\n\\n- Good constraint scoping -- limiting changes to `attach.go` and helpers avoids regression risk in the core strategy/lifecycle code.\\n- The gap analysis table in the \\\"Observed Gaps\\\" section clearly communicates what is missing and the impact.\\n- Fix 6 (attribution) correctly identifies that existing code already handles this and only needs test verification.\\n- The spec correctly identifies that `SaveStep` picks up `prompt.txt` from the metadata directory, which is how the shadow branch gets it.\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\n**Overall assessment: REQUEST CHANGES**\\n\\nThe spec is well-structured and identifies the right gaps, but has several factual errors that would lead to bugs if implemented as-written:\\n\\n1. **Gemini message type is `\\\"user\\\"`, not `\\\"human\\\"`** -- this would produce empty prompts for Gemini sessions, defeating Fix 2's purpose.\\n2. **Token calculation should use the higher-level `agent.CalculateTokenUsage()` function** rather than the low-level `AsTokenCalculator` directly, to get subagent support and consistent error handling.\\n3. **Model extraction from Gemini transcripts is not feasible** with the current transcript format -- the spec needs to acknowledge this or propose an alternative (e.g., reading the model hint file if available).\\n4. **Timestamp extraction for duration is agent-dependent** and not possible for Gemini.\\n\\nThere are also existing utility functions in the codebase (`geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts`, `agent.CalculateTokenUsage`) that the spec should reference rather than proposing new implementations that duplicate existing logic.\\n\\n**Estimated effort to address:** 1-2 hours to revise the spec with corrections.\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\