ile, []byte(firstPrompt), 0o600); err != nil {\\n    41→        logging.Warn(logCtx, \\\"failed to write prompt file\\\", \\\"error\\\", err)\\n    42→    }\\n    43→}\\n    44→```\\n    45→\\n    46→This ensures `SaveStep` picks up `prompt.txt` when copying the metadata dir to the shadow branch, and `CondenseSession` finds it when extracting session data.\\n    47→\\n    48→### Fix 2: Extract prompts from Gemini transcripts\\n    49→\\n    50→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` (modify `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript`)\\n    51→\\n    52→The current implementation only uses `transcript.ParseFromBytes()` which parses JSONL (Claude Code format). Add a fallback for Gemini's JSON format:\\n    53→\\n    54→```go\\n    55→func extractFirstPromptFromTranscript(data []byte) string {\\n    56→    // Try JSONL format first (Claude Code, OpenCode, etc.)\\n    57→    lines, err := transcript.ParseFromBytes(data)\\n    58→    if err == nil {\\n    59→        for _, line := range lines {\\n    60→            if line.Type == transcript.TypeUser {\\n    61→                if prompt := extractTextFromMessage(line.Message); prompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    62→                    return prompt\\n    63→                }\\n    64→            }\\n    65→        }\\n    66→    }\\n    67→\\n    68→    // Fallback: try Gemini JSON format {\\\"messages\\\": [...]}\\n    69→    return extractFirstPromptFromGeminiTranscript(data)\\n    70→}\\n    71→```\\n    72→\\n    73→New helper `extractFirstPromptFromGeminiTranscript`:\\n    74→- Parse as `{\\\"messages\\\": [...]}`\\n    75→- Find first message with `\\\"type\\\": \\\"human\\\"` (Gemini's user message type)\\n    76→- Extract text content from the message parts\\n    77→\\n    78→### Fix 3: Calculate token usage\\n    79→\\n    80→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n    81→\\n    82→After reading the transcript, if the agent implements `TokenCalculator`, calculate usage:\\n    83→\\n    84→```go\\n    85→if calc, ok := agent.AsTokenCalculator(ag); ok {\\n    86→    if usage, err := calc.CalculateTokenUsage(transcriptData, 0); err == nil && usage != nil {\\n    87→        state.TokenUsage = usage\\n    88→    }\\n    89→}\\n    90→```\\n    91→\\n    92→This must happen after `InitializeSession` and before `SaveStep`, updating the session state so that `CondenseSession` picks it up.\\n    93→\\n    94→### Fix 4: Extract model name from transcript\\n    95→\\n    96→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n    97→\\n    98→Add a helper that extracts the model name from the transcript:\\n    99→- **Claude Code:** Look for `\\\"model\\\"` field in assistant messages\\n   100→- **Gemini:** Look for model info in message metadata or `beforeModel` hook data\\n   101→\\n   102→Set `state.ModelName` before `SaveStep`.\\n   103→\\n   104→### Fix 5: Set session metrics from transcript\\n   105→\\n   106→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n   107→\\n   108→Count user messages in the transcript to determine turn count. Estimate duration from first/last message timestamps if available:\\n   109→\\n   110→```go\\n   111→state.SessionTurnCount = countUserTurns(transcriptData, ag)\\n   112→if firstTS, lastTS := extractTimestampRange(transcriptData); !firstTS.IsZero() {\\n   113→    state.SessionDurationMs = int64(lastTS.Sub(firstTS).Milliseconds())\\n   114→}\\n   115→```\\n   116→\\n   117→### Fix 6: Ensure attribution populates correctly\\n   118→\\n   119→`InitializeSession()` already calculates `PendingPromptAttribution` (comparing working tree state against HEAD). This flows through `SaveStep` into the session state's `PromptAttributions` array, which `CondenseSession` uses for `initial_attribution`.\\n   120→\\n   121→Verify this works correctly for attach by ensuring `SaveStep` receives the full file change list. The current code already passes `relModifiedFiles`, `relNewFiles`, and `relDeletedFiles` to `StepContext` — no change needed here, just verification via tests.\\n   122→\\n   123→## File Change