ch.go` | Write `prompt.txt`, calculate token usage, extract model, set session metrics, update `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` to handle Gemini |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/attach_test.go` | Tests for all new behavior |\\n\\n## Testing\\n\\n- Unit tests: `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` with Claude Code JSONL and Gemini JSON transcripts\\n- Unit tests: token usage calculation, model extraction, turn counting for both formats\\n- Integration test: full attach flow produces checkpoint with `prompt.txt`, populated token usage, session metrics, and attribution\\n- E2E canary (Vogon): if attach is exercised in E2E tests, verify checkpoint data completeness\\n- Manual verification: `entire attach <gemini-session-id> --agent gemini` produces a checkpoint visible in UI\\n\\n## Out of Scope\\n\\n- Changes to strategy, checkpoint, or lifecycle code\\n- Changes to the push flow (pre-push hook already works correctly)\\n- UI changes\\n- New agent implementations\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[{\"oldStart\":6,\"oldLines\":9,\"newStart\":6,\"newLines\":9,\"lines\":[\" \",\" ## Problem\",\" \",\"-Checkpoints created by `entire attach` are incomplete compared to those created by the normal hook flow (SessionStart → TurnStart → TurnEnd → PostCommit). The UI at entire.io cannot render attach-created checkpoints because critical data is missing.\",\"+Checkpoints created by `entire attach` are incomplete compared to those created by the normal hook flow (SessionStart -> TurnStart -> TurnEnd -> PostCommit). The UI at entire.io cannot render attach-created checkpoints because critical data is missing.\",\" \",\"-**Root cause:** The attach flow calls `InitializeSession()` → `SaveStep()` → `CondenseSession()` but skips the intermediate lifecycle steps that populate session state and write artifacts like `prompt.txt`.\",\"+**Root cause:** The attach flow calls `InitializeSession()` -> `SaveStep()` -> `CondenseSession()` but skips the intermediate lifecycle steps that populate session state and wri