pty prompts |\\n    19→| Token usage | `CalculateTokenUsage()` called in TurnEnd | **Not calculated** | Empty `token_usage` in metadata |\\n    20→| Model name | Provided by hook events | **Not extracted** | Empty `model` field in metadata |\\n    21→| Session metrics (turn_count) | `persistEventMetadataToState()` in PostCommit | **Not set** | Missing `session_metrics` in metadata |\\n    22→| `state.LastPrompt` | Set by `InitializeSession` from hook prompt | Set but may be empty for Gemini | Missing prompt display |\\n    23→\\n    24→## Constraints\\n    25→\\n    26→- **Do not alter existing strategy, checkpoint, or lifecycle logic.** All fixes are scoped to `attach.go` and supporting helpers.\\n    27→- The existing pipeline (SaveStep -> CondenseSession -> WriteCommitted) works correctly when given complete input data. The fix is to ensure attach provides complete data.\\n    28→- Must work for all registered agents: claude-code, gemini, opencode, cursor, copilot-cli, factoryai-droid.\\n    29→- Model name and session duration are **best-effort** — not all transcript formats include this data.\\n    30→\\n    31→## Design\\n    32→\\n    33→### Fix 1: Write `prompt.txt` to metadata dir before SaveStep\\n    34→\\n    35→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n    36→\\n    37→After extracting `firstPrompt` (line 169) and creating the metadata directory (line 154), write the prompt file:\\n    38→\\n    39→```go\\n    40→if firstPrompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    41→    promptFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.PromptFileName)\\n    42→    if err := os.WriteFile(promptFile, []byte(firstPrompt), 0o600); err != nil {\\n    43→        logging.Warn(logCtx, \\\"failed to write prompt file\\\", \\\"error\\\", err)\\n    44→    }\\n    45→}\\n    46→```\\n    47→\\n    48→This ensures `SaveStep` picks up `prompt.txt` when copying the metadata dir to the shadow branch, and `CondenseSession` finds it when extracting session data.\\n    49→\\n    50→### Fix 2: Extract prompts from Gemini transcripts\\n    51→\\n    52→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` (modify `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript`)\\n    53→\\n    54→The current implementation only uses `transcript.ParseFromBytes()` which parses JSONL (Claude Code format). Add a fallback that reuses the existing Gemini transcript parser.\\n    55→\\n    56→```go\\n    57→func extractFirstPromptFromTranscript(data []byte) string {\\n    58→    // Try JSONL format first (Claude Code, OpenCode, etc.)\\n    59→    lines, err := transcript.ParseFromBytes(data)\\n    60→    if err == nil {\\n    61→        for _, line := range lines {\\n    62→            if line.Type == transcript.TypeUser {\\n    63→                if prompt := extractTextFromMessage(line.Message); prompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    64→                    return prompt\\n    65→                }\\n    66→            }\\n    67→        }\\n    68→    }\\n    69→\\n    70→    // Fallback: try Gemini JSON format {\\\"messages\\\": [...]}\\n    71→    // Reuse geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts which already handles\\n    72→    // Gemini's {\\\"messages\\\": [...]} format with \\\"type\\\": \\\"user\\\" messages.\\n    73→    if prompts := geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts(data); len(prompts) > 0 {\\n    74→        return prompts[0]\\n    75→    }\\n    76→\\n    77→    return \\\"\\\"\\n    78→}\\n    79→```\\n    80→\\n    81→**Key correction from review:** Gemini uses `\\\"type\\\": \\\"user\\\"` (not `\\\"human\\\"`), and `geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts` (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/transcript.go:154`) already does this extraction. Reuse it rather than reimplementing.\\n    82→\\n    83→### Fix 3: Calculate token usage\\n    84→\\n    85→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n    86→\\n    87→Use the higher-level `agent.CalculateTokenUsage()` helper (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/token_usage.go:13`) which handles `SubagentAwareExtractor` and error logging:\\n    88→\\n    89→```go\\n    90→if usage := agent.CalculateTokenUsage(ctx, ag, transcriptData, 0); usage != nil {\\n    91→    state.TokenUsage = usage\\n    92→}\\n    93→```\\n    94→\\n    95→This must happen after `InitializeSession` and before `SaveSessionState`, updating the session state so `CondenseSession` picks it up.\\n    96→\\n    97→**Note:** Condensation recalculates token usage from the transcript and overwrites `state.TokenUsage`. Setting it here ensures correct data even if condensation fails (shadow-branch-only path).\\n    98→\\n    99→### Fix 4: Extract model name from transcript (best-effort)\\n   100→\\n   101→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n   102→\\n   103→- **Claude Code:** Parse transcript for `\\\"model\\\"` field in assistant messages (JSONL format includes model per message).\\n   104→- **Gemini:** Model info comes from `BeforeModel` hook events, not stored in the transcript. Leave empty — this is acceptable as a best-effort field.\\n   105→- **Other agents:** Leave empty if not extractable.\\n   106→\\n   107→Set `state.ModelName` before `SaveSessionState`. Since `InitializeSession` already receives model as `\\\"\\\"` for attach, we update state directly:\\n   108→\\n   109→```go\\n   110→if model := extractModelFromTranscript(transcriptData, agentName); model != \\\"\\\" {\\n   111→    state.ModelName = model\\n   112→}\\n   113→```\\n   114→\\n   115→### Fix 5: Set session metrics from transcript\\n   116→\\n   117→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n   118→\\n   119→Count user messages in the transcript to determine turn count:\\n   120→\\n   121→```go\\n   122→state.SessionTurnCount = countUserTurns(transcriptData, agentName)\\n   123→```\\n   124→\\n   125→For turn counting:\\n   126→- **JSONL agents:** Count lines with `transcript.TypeUser`\\n   127→- **Gemini:** Count messages with `\\\"type\\\": \\\"user\\\"` (reuse `geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts` length)\\n   128→\\n   129→**Duration:** Best-effort from timestamps in transcript messages. Claude Code JSONL includes `\\\"timestamp\\\"` fields. Gemini messages do not include timestamps, so duration stays zero for Gemini.\\n   130→\\n   131→```go\\n   132→if dur := estimateSessionDuration(transcriptData, agentName); dur > 0 {\\n   133→    state.SessionDurationMs = dur\\n   134→}\\n   135→```\\n   136→\\n   137→### Fix 6: Ensure attribution populates correctly\\n   138→\\n   139→`InitializeSession()` already calculates `PendingPromptAttribution` (comparing working tree state against HEAD). This flows through `SaveStep` into the session state's `PromptAttributions` array, which `CondenseSession` uses for `initial_attribution`.\\n   140→\\n   141→No code change needed — verify via tests that the existing path works for attach.\\n   142→\\n   143→## File Changes Summary\\n   144→\\n   145→| File | Change |\\n   146→|------|--------|\\n   147→| `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` | Write `prompt.txt`, calculate token usage, extract model, set session metrics, update `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` to handle Gemini |\\n   148→| `cmd/entire/cli/attach_test.go` | Tests for all new behavior |\\n   149→\\n   150→## Testing\\n   151→\\n   152→- Unit tests: `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` with Claude Code JSONL and Gemini JSON transcripts\\n   153→- Unit tests: token usage calculation, model extraction, turn counting for both formats\\n   154→- Integration test: full attach flow produces checkpoint with `prompt.txt`, populated token usage, session metrics, and attribution\\n   155→- E2E canary (Vogon): if attach is exercised in E2E tests, verify checkpoint data completeness\\n   156→- Manual verification: `entire attach <gemini-session-id> --agent gemini` produces a checkpoint visible in UI\\n   157→\\n   158→## Out of Scope\\n   159→\\n   160→- Changes to strategy, checkpoint, or lifecycle code\\n   161→- Changes to the push flow (pre-push hook already works correctly)\\n   162→- UI changes\\n   163→- New agent implementations\\n   164→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"ac76e7a3-0559-4842-8422-36a113786e09\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:50:50.317Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-03-12-attach-checkpoint-parity-design.md\",\"content\":\"# Attach Checkpoint Parity\\n\\n**Date:** 2026-03-12\\n**Status:** Draft\\n**Branch:** attach-session-id\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\nCheckpoints created by `entire attach` are incomplete compared to those created by the normal hook flow (SessionStart -> TurnStart -> TurnEnd -> PostCommit). The UI at entire.io cannot render attach-created checkpoints because critical data is missing.\\n\\n**Root cause:** The attach flow calls `InitializeSession()` -> `SaveStep()` -> `CondenseSession()` but skips the intermediate lifecycle steps that populate session state and write artifacts like `prompt.txt`.\\n\\n## Observed Gaps\\n\\n| Data Item | Hook Flow | Attach Flow | Impact |\\n|-----------|-----------|-------------|--------|\\n| `prompt.txt` in metadata dir | Written by TurnStart handler | **Not written** | UI cannot render checkpoint (blocker) |\\n| Prompt extraction for Gemini | N/A (hooks provide prompt) | `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` only parses JSONL | Gemini sessions get empty prompts |\\n| Token usage | `CalculateTokenUsage()` called in TurnEnd | **Not calculated** | Empty `token_usage` in metadata |\\n| Model name | Provided by hook events | **Not extracted** | Empty `model` field in metadata |\\n| Session metrics (turn_count) | `persistEventMetadataToState()` in PostCommit | **Not set** | Missing `session_metrics` in metadata |\\n| `state.LastPrompt` | Set by `InitializeSession` from hook prompt | Set but may be empty for Gemini | Missing prompt display |\\n\\n## Constraints\\n\\n- **Do not alter existing strategy, checkpoint, or lifecycle logic.** All fixes are scoped to `attach.go` and supporting helpers.\\n- The existing pipeline (SaveStep -> CondenseSession -> WriteCommitted) works correctly when given complete input data. The fix is to ensure attach provides complete data.\\n- Must work for all registered agents: claude-code, gemini, opencode, cursor, copilot-cli, factoryai-droid.\\n- Model name and session duration are **best-effort** — not all transcript formats include this data.\\n\\n## Design\\n\\n### Fix 1: Write `prompt.txt` to metadata dir before SaveStep\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n\\nAfter extracting `firstPrompt` (line 169) and creating the metadata directory (line 154), write the prompt file:\\n\\n```go\\nif firstPrompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    promptFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.PromptFileName)\\n    if err := os.WriteFile(promptFile, []byte(firstPrompt), 0o600); err != nil {\\n        logging.Warn(logCtx, \\\"failed to write prompt file\\\", \\\"error\\\", err)\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis ensures `SaveStep` picks up `prompt.txt` when copying the metadata dir to the shadow branch, and `CondenseSession` finds it when extracting session data.\\n\\n### Fix 2: Extract prompts from Gemini transcripts\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` (modify `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript`)\\n\\nThe current implementation only uses `transcript.ParseFromBytes()` which parses JSONL (Claude Code format). Add a fallback that reuses the existing Gemini transcript parser.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc extractFirstPromptFromTranscript(data []byte) string {\\n    // Try JSONL format first (Claude Code, OpenCode, etc.)\\n    lines, err := transcript.ParseFromBytes(data)\\n    if err == nil {\\n        for _, line := range lines {\\n            if line.Type == transcript.TypeUser {\\n                if prompt := extractTextFromMessage(line.Message); prompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n                    return prompt\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    // Fallback: try Gemini JSON format {\\\"messages\\\": [...]}\\n    // Reuse geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts which already handles\\n    // Gemini's {\\\"messages\\\": [...]} format with \\\"type\\\": \\\"user\\\" messages.\\n    if prompts := geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts(data); len(prompts) > 0 {\\n        return prompts[0]\\n    }\\n\\n    return \\\"\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key correction from review:** Gemini uses `\\\"type\\\": \\\"user\\\"` (not `\\\"human\\\"`), and `geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts` (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/transcript.go:154`) already does this extraction. Reuse it rather than reimplementing.\\n\\n### Fix 3: Calculate token usage\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n\\nUse the higher-level `agent.CalculateTokenUsage()` helper (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/token_usage.go:13`) which handles `SubagentAwareExtractor` and error logging:\\n\\n```go\\nif usage := agent.CalculateTokenUsage(ctx, ag, transcriptData, 0); usage != nil {\\n    state.TokenUsage = usage\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis must happen after `InitializeSession` and before `SaveSessionState`, updating the session state so `CondenseSession` picks it up.\\n\\n**Note:** Condensation recalculates token usage from the transcript and overwrites `state.TokenUsage`. Setting it here ensures correct data even if condensation fails (shadow-branch-only path).\\n\\n### Fix 4: Extract model name from transcript (best-effort)\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n\\n- **Claude Code:** Parse transcript for `\\\"model\\\"` field in assistant messages (JSONL format includes model per message).\\n- **Gemini:** Model info comes from `BeforeModel` hook events, not stored in the transcript. Leave empty — this is acceptable as a best-effort field.\\n- **Other agents:** Leave empty if not extractable.\\n\\nSet `state.ModelName` before `SaveSessionState`. Since `InitializeSession` already receives model as `\\\"\\\"` for attach, we update state directly:\\n\\n```go\\nif model := extractModelFromTranscript(transcriptData, agentName); model != \\\"\\\" {\\n    state.ModelName = model\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Fix 5: Set session metrics from transcript\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n\\nCount user messages in the transcript to determine turn count:\\n\\n```go\\nstate.SessionTurnCount = countUserTurns(transcriptData, agentName)\\n```\\n\\nFor turn counting:\\n- **JSONL agents:** Count lines with `transcript.TypeUser`\\n- **Gemini:** Count messages with `\\\"type\\\": \\\"user\\\"` (reuse `geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts` length)\\n\\n**Duration:** Best-effort from timestamps in transcript messages. Claude Code JSONL includes `\\\"timestamp\\\"` fields. Gemini messages do not include timestamps, so duration stays zero for Gemini.\\n\\n```go\\nif dur := estimateSessionDuration(transcriptData, agentName); dur > 0 {\\n    state.SessionDurationMs = dur\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Fix 6: Ensure attribution populates correctly\\n\\n`InitializeSession()` already calculates `PendingPromptAttribution` (comparing working tree state against HEAD). This flows through `SaveStep` into the session state's `PromptAttributions` array, which `CondenseSession` uses for `initial_attribution`.\\n\\nNo code change needed — verify via tests that the existing path works for attach.\\n\\n## File Changes Summary\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` | Write `prompt.txt`, calculate token usage, extract model, set session metrics, update `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` to handle Gemini |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/attach_test.go` | Tests for all new behavior |\\n\\n## Testing\\n\\n- Unit tests: `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` with Claude Code JSONL and Gemini JSON transcripts\\n- Unit tests: token usage calculation, model extraction, turn counting for both formats\\n- Integration test: full attach flow produces checkpoint with `prompt.txt`, populated token usage, session metrics, and attribution\\n- E2E canary (Vogon): if attach is exercised in E2E tests, verify checkpoint data completeness\\n- Manual verification: `entire attach <gemini-session-id> --agent gemini` produces a checkpoint visible in UI\\n\\n## Out of Scope\\n\\n- Changes to strategy, checkpoint, or lifecycle code\\n- Changes to the push flow (pre-push hook alr