rmediate lifecycle steps that populate session state and write artifacts like `prompt.txt`.\\n    12→\\n    13→## Observed Gaps\\n    14→\\n    15→| Data Item | Hook Flow | Attach Flow | Impact |\\n    16→|-----------|-----------|-------------|--------|\\n    17→| `prompt.txt` in metadata dir | Written by TurnStart handler | **Not written** | UI cannot render checkpoint (blocker) |\\n    18→| Prompt extraction for Gemini | N/A (hooks provide prompt) | `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` only parses JSONL | Gemini sessions get empty prompts |\\n    19→| Token usage | `CalculateTokenUsage()` called in TurnEnd | **Not calculated** | Empty `token_usage` in metadata |\\n    20→| Model name | Provided by hook events | **Not extracted** | Empty `model` field in metadata |\\n    21→| Session metrics (turn_count) | `persistEventMetadataToState()` in PostCommit | **Not set** | Missing `session_metrics` in metadata |\\n    22→| `state.LastPrompt` | Set by `InitializeSession` from hook prompt | Set but may be empty for Gemini | Missing prompt display |\\n    23→\\n    24→## Constraints\\n    25→\\n    26→- **Do not alter existing strategy, checkpoint, or lifecycle logic.** All fixes are scoped to `attach.go` and supporting helpers.\\n    27→- The existing pipeline (SaveStep -> CondenseSession -> WriteCommitted) works correctly when given complete input data. The fix is to ensure attach provides complete data.\\n    28→- Must work for all registered agents: claude-code, gemini, opencode, cursor, copilot-cli, factoryai-droid.\\n    29→- Model name and session duration are **best-effort** — not all transcript formats include this data.\\n    30→\\n    31→## Design\\n    32→\\n    33→### Fix 1: Write `prompt.txt` to metadata dir before SaveStep\\n    34→\\n    35→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n    36→\\n    37→After extracting `firstPrompt` (line 169) and creating the metadata directory (line 154), write the prompt file:\\n    38→\\n    39→```go\\n    40→if firstPrompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    41→    promptFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.PromptFileName)\\n    42→    if err := os.WriteFile(promptFile, []byte(firstPrompt), 0o600); err != nil {\\n    43→        logging.Warn(logCtx, \\\"failed to write prompt file\\\", \\\"error\\\", err)\\n    44→    }\\n    45→}\\n    46→```\\n    47→\\n    48→This ensures `SaveStep` picks up `prompt.txt` when copying the metadata dir to the shadow branch, and `CondenseSession` finds it when extracting session data.\\n    49→\\n    50→### Fix 2: Extract prompts from Gemini transcripts\\n    51→\\n    52→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` (modify `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript`)\\n    53→\\n    54→The current implementation only uses `transcript.ParseFromBytes()` which parses JSONL (Claude Code format). Add a fallback that reuses the existing Gemini transcript parser.\\n    55→\\n    56→```go\\n    57→func extractFirstPromptFromTranscript(data []byte) string {\\n    58→    // Try JSONL format first (Claude Code, OpenCode, etc.)\\n    59→    lines, err := transcript.ParseFromBytes(data)\\n    60→    if err == nil {\\n    61→        for _, line := range lines {\\n    62→            if line.Type == transcript.TypeUser {\\n    63→                if prompt := extractTextFromMessage(line.Message); prompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    64→                    return prompt\\n    65→                }\\n    66→            }\\n    67→        }\\n    68→    }\\n    69→\\n    70→    // Fallback: try Gemini JSON format {\\\"messages\\\": [...]}\\n    71→    // Reuse geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts which already handles\\n    72→    // Gemini's {\\\"messages\\\": [...]} format with \\\"type\\\": \\\"user\\\" messages.\\n    73→    if prompts := geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts(data); len(prompts) > 0 {\\n    74→        return prompts[0]\\n    75→    }\\n    76→\\n    77→    return \\\"\\\"\\n    78→}\\n    79→```\\n    80→\\n    81→**Key correction from review:** Gemini uses `\\\"type\\\": \\\"user\\\"` (not `\\\"human\\\"`), and `geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts` (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/transcript.go:154`) already does this extraction. Reuse it rather than reimplementing.\\n    82→\\n    83→### Fix 3: Calculate token usage\\n    84→\\n    85→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n    86→\\n    87→Use the higher-level `agent.CalculateTokenUsage()` helper (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/token_usage.go:13`) which handles `SubagentAwareExtractor` and error logging:\\n    88→\\n    89→```go\\n    90→if usage := agent.CalculateTokenUsage(ctx, ag, transcriptData, 0); usage != nil {\\n    91→    state.TokenUsage = usage\\n    92→}\\n    93→```\\n    94→\\n    95→This must happen after `InitializeSession` and before `SaveSessionState`, updating the session state so `CondenseSession` picks it up.\\n    96→\\n    97→**Note:** Condensation recalculates token usage from the transcript and overwrites `state.TokenUsage`. Setting it here ensures correct data even if condensation fails (shadow-branch-only path).\\n    98→\\n    99→### Fix 4: Extract model name from transcript (best-effort)\\n   100→\\n   101→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n   102→\\n   103→- **Claude Code:** Parse transcript for `\\\"model\\\"` field in assistant messages (JSONL format includes model per message).\\n   104→- **Gemini:** Model info comes from `BeforeModel` hook events, not stored in the transcript. Leave empty — this is acceptable as a best-effort field.\\n   105→- **Other agents:** Leave empty if not extractable.\\n   106→\\n   107→Set `state.ModelName` before `SaveSessionState`. Since `InitializeSession` already receives model as `\\\"\\\"` for attach, we update state directly:\\n   108→\\n   109→```go\\n   110→if model := extractModelFromTranscript(transcriptData, agentName); model != \\\"\\\" {\\n   111→    state.ModelName = model\\n   112→}\\n   113→```\\n   114→\\n   115→### Fix 5: Set session metrics from transcript\\n   116→\\n   117→**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`\\n   118→\\n   119→Count user messages in the transcript to determine turn count:\\n   120→\\n   121→```go\\n   122→state.SessionTurnCount = countUserTurns(transcriptData, agentName)\\n   123→```\\n   124→\\n   125→For turn counting:\\n   126→- **JSONL agents:** Count lines with `transcript.TypeUser`\\n   127→- **Gemini:** Count messages with `\\\"type\\\": \\\"user\\\"` (reuse `geminicli.ExtractAllUserPrompts` length)\\n   128→\\n   129→**Duration:** Best-effort from timestamps in transcript messages. Claude Code JSONL includes `\\\"timestamp\\\"` fields. Gemini messages do not include timestamps, so duration stays zero for Gemini.\\n   130→\\n   131→```go\\n   132→if dur := estimateSessionDuration(transcriptData, agentName); dur > 0 {\\n   133→    state.SessionDurationMs = dur\\n   134→}\\n   135→```\\n   136→\\n   137→### Fix 6: Ensure attribution populates correctly\\n   138→\\n   139→`InitializeSession()` already calculates `PendingPromptAttribution` (comparing working tree state against HEAD). This flows through `SaveStep` into the session state's `PromptAttributions` array, which `CondenseSession` uses for `initial_attribution`.\\n   140→\\n   141→No code change needed — verify via tests that the existing path works for attach.\\n   142→\\n   143→## File Changes Summary\\n   144→\\n   145→| File | Change |\\n   146→|------|--------|\\n   147→| `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go` | Write `prompt.txt`, calculate token usage, extract model, set session metrics, update `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` to handle Gemini |\\n   148→| `cmd/entire/cli/attach_test.go` | Tests for all new behavior |\\n   149→\\n   150→## Testing\\n   151→\\n   152→- Unit tests: `extractFirstPromptFromTranscript` with Claude Code JSONL and Gemini JSON transcripts\\n   153→- Unit tests: token usage calculation, model extraction, turn counting for both formats\\n   154→- Integration test: full attach flow produces checkpoint with `prompt.txt`, populated token usage, session metrics, and attribution\\n   155→- E2E canary (Vogon): if attach is exercised in E2E tests, verify checkpoint data completeness\\n   156→- Manual verification: `entire attach <gemini-session-id> --agent gemini` produces a checkpoint visible in UI\\n   157→\\n   158→## Out of Scope\\n   159→\\n   160→- Changes to strategy, checkpoint, or lifecycle code\\n   161→- Changes to the push flow (pre-push hook already works correctly)\\n   162→- UI changes\\n   163→- New agent implementations\\n   164→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"277738c3-3945-4a99-8d40-5fa5d36761a3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:53:08.001Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"abd9c75d4ca4f20c1\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01N5f6K5tSoQg7hwaVTodhki\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CSrNk4CarZebr4jS4rwkA8\",\"uuid\":\"9584bfeb-0c63-4c45-b37f-7431605b8535\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:53:08.470Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"61b0a478-d835-45a6-936a-9d30f7ba786c\",\"version\":\"2.1.74\",\"gitBranch\":\"attach-session-id\",\"slug\":\"fancy-dreaming-biscuit\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9584bfeb-0c63-4c45-b37f-7431605b8535\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:53:08.501Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01GQJFuhHuWy1WgCvkAeb3PK\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01XpL1wt4piUJi1yYbVe199W\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":10563,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":6878,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":10563,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYyrEPt2EJr3pv1SNJ6GB\",\"uuid\":\"b6228f2a-bc2e-4531-99a2-e8f43872f018\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"abd9c75d4ca4f20c1\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01N5f6K5tSoQg7hwaVTodhki\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CSrNk4CarZebr4jS4rwkA8\",\"uuid\":\"d4ebeab6-7ec1-4e81-b86c-7d75e55f0e86\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T20:53:08.501Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"61b0a478-d835-45a6-936a-9d30f7ba786c\",\"version\":\"2.1.74\",\"gitBranch\":\"attach-session-id\",\"slug\":\"fancy-dreaming-biscuit\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d4ebeab6-7ec1-4e81-b86c-7d75e55f0e86\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01XpL1wt4piUJi1yYbVe199W\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→package cli\\n     2→\\n     3→import (\\n     4→\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n     5→\\t\\\"encoding/json\\\"\\n     6→\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n     7→\\t\\\"io\\\"\\n     8→\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n     9→\\t\\\"os/exec\\\"\\n    10→\\t\\\"path/filepath\\\"\\n    11→\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n    12→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n    13→\\n    14→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent\\\"\\n    15→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/types\\\"\\n    16→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/logging\\\"\\n    17→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths\\\"\\n    18→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/session\\\"\\n    19→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy\\\"\\n    20→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trailers\\\"\\n    21→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/transcript\\\"\\n    22→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/validation\\\"\\n    23→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/versioninfo\\\"\\n    24→\\n    25→\\t\\\"github.com/charmbracelet/huh\\\"\\n    26→\\t\\\"github.com/spf13/cobra\\\"\\n    27→)\\n    28→\\n    29→func newAttachCmd() *cobra.Command {\\n    30→\\tvar (\\n    31→\\t\\tforce     bool\\n    32→\\t\\tagentFlag string\\n    33→\\t)\\n    34→\\tcmd := &cobra.Command{\\n    35→\\t\\tUse:   \\\"attach <session-id>\\\",\\n    36→\\t\\tShort: \\\"Attach an existing agent session\\\",\\n    37→\\t\\tLong: `Attach an existing agent session that wasn't captured by hooks.\\n    38→\\n    39→This creates a checkpoint from the session's transcript and registers the\\n    40→session for future tracking. Use this when hooks failed to fire or weren't\\n    41→installed when the session started.\\n    42→\\n    43→Supported agents: claude-code, gemini, opencode, cursor, copilot-cli, factoryai-droid`,\\n    44→\\t\\tArgs: cobra.ExactArgs(1),\\n    45→\\t\\tRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\\n    46→\\t\\t\\tif checkDisabledGuard(cmd.Context(), cmd.OutOrStdout()) {\\n    47→\\t\\t\\t\\treturn nil\\n    48→\\t\\t\\t}\\n    49→\\t\\t\\tagentName := types.AgentName(agentFlag)\\n    50→\\t\\t\\treturn runAttach(cmd.Context(), cmd.OutOrStdout(), args[0], agentName, force)\\n    51→\\t\\t},\\n    52→\\t}\\n    53→\\tcmd.Flags().BoolVarP(&force, \\\"force\\\", \\\"f\\\", false, \\\"Skip confirmation and amend the last commit with the checkpoint trailer\\\")\\n    54→\\tcmd.Flags().StringVarP(&agentFlag, \\\"agent\\\", \\\"a\\\", string(agent.DefaultAgentName), \\\"Agent that created the session (claude-code, gemini, opencode, cursor, copilot-cli, factoryai-droid)\\\")\\n    55→\\treturn cmd\\n    56→}\\n    57→\\n    58→func runAttach(ctx context.Context, w io.Writer, sessionID string, agentName types.AgentName, force bool) error {\\n    59→\\tlogCtx := logging.WithComponent(ctx, \\\"attach\\\")\\n    60→\\n    61→\\t// Validate session ID format\\n    62→\\tif err := validation.ValidateSessionID(sessionID); err != nil {\\n    63→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"invalid session ID: %w\\\", err)\\n    64→\\t}\\n    65→\\n    66→\\t// Ensure we're in a git repo\\n    67→\\trepoRoot, err := paths.WorktreeRoot(ctx)\\n    68→\\tif err != nil {\\n    69→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"not a git repository: %w\\\", err)\\n    70→\\t}\\n    71→\\n    72→\\t// Check session isn't already tracked\\n    73→\\tstore, err := session.NewStateStore(ctx)\\n    74→\\tif err != nil {\\n    75→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to open session store: %w\\\", err)\\n    76→\\t}\\n    77→\\texisting, err := store.Load(ctx, sessionID)\\n    78→\\tif err != nil {\\n    79→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to check existing session: %w\\\", err)\\n    80→\\t}\\n    81→\\tif existing != nil {\\n    82→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"session %s is already tracked by Entire\\\", sessionID)\\n    83→\\t}\\n    84→\\n    85→\\t// Resolve agent and transcript path\\n    86→\\tag, err := agent.Get(agentName)\\n    87→\\tif err != nil {\\n    88→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"agent %q not available: %w\\\", agentName, err)\\n    89→\\t}\\n    90→\\tagentType := ag.Type()\\n    91→\\n    92→\\ttranscriptPath, err := resolveTranscriptPath(ctx, sessionID, ag)\\n    93→\\tif err != nil {\\n    94→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to resolve transcript path: %w\\\", err)\\n    95→\\t}\\n    96→\\t// Agents use cwd-derived project directories, so the transcript may be stored under\\n    97→\\t// a different project directory if the session was started from a different working directory.\\n    98→\\tif _, statErr := os.Stat(transcriptPath); statErr != nil {\\n    99→\\t\\tif found, searchErr := searchTranscriptInProjectDirs(agentName, sessionID, ag); searchErr == nil {\\n   100→\\t\\t\\tlogging.Info(logCtx, \\\"found transcript in alternative project directory\\\", \\\"path\\\", found)\\n   101→\\t\\t\\ttranscriptPath = found\\n   102→\\t\\t} else {\\n   103→\\t\\t\\tlogging.Debug(logCtx, \\\"fallback transcript search failed\\\", \\\"error\\\", searchErr)\\n   104→\\t\\t}\\n   105→\\t}\\n   106→\\tif _, statErr := os.Stat(transcriptPath); statErr != nil {\\n   107→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"transcript not found at %s; is the session ID correct?